OR {
AttackStep CVE202430259 description="FastDDS is a C++ implementation of the DDS (Data Distribution Service) standard of the OMG (Object Management Group). Prior to versions 2.14.1, 2.13.5, 2.10.4, and 2.6.8, when a publisher serves malformed `RTPS` packet, heap buffer overflow occurs on the subscriber. This can remotely crash any Fast-DDS process, potentially leading to a DOS attack. Versions 2.14.1, 2.13.5, 2.10.4, and 2.6.8 contain a patch for the issue.
" CVE=CVE-2024-30259 CVSS=CVSS:3.1/AV:N/AC:L/PR:N/UI:N/S:U/C:N/I:L/A:H BaseScore=8.2 ImpactScore=4.2 ExploitabilityScore=3.9
